uk.gov.gchq.palisade.resource.service

Class HDFSResourceService

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.gov.gchq.palisade.resource.service.HDFSResourceService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResourceService, Service

    public class HDFSResourceService
extends Object
implements ResourceService
    A implementation of the ResourceService for HDFS.

    This service is for the retrieval of Resources only. Resources cannot be added via this service, they should be added through the actual real HDFS.

      • getResourcesByResource

        public CompletableFuture<Map<LeafResource,ConnectionDetail>> getResourcesByResource(GetResourcesByResourceRequest request)
        Description copied from interface: ResourceService
        Get a list of resources based on a specific resource. This allows for the retrieval of the appropriate ConnectionDetails for a given resource. It may also be used to retrieve the details all the resources that are notionally children of another resource. For example, in a standard hierarchical filing system the files in a directory could be considered child resources and calling this method on the directory resource would fetch the details on the contained files.
        Specified by:
        getResourcesByResource in interface ResourceService
        Parameters:
        request - the details of the resource to request
        Returns:
        a CompletableFuture that upon completion will contain a map of how to retrieve the available resources

        Specified by:

      • getResourcesByType

        public CompletableFuture<Map<LeafResource,ConnectionDetail>> getResourcesByType(GetResourcesByTypeRequest request)
        Description copied from interface: ResourceService
        Obtain a list of resources that match a specifc resource type. This method allows a client to obtain potentially large collections of resources by requesting all the resources of one particular type. For example, a client may request all "employee contact card" records. Please note the warning in the class documentation above, that just because a resource is available does not guarantee that the requesting client has the right to access it.
        Specified by:
        getResourcesByType in interface ResourceService
        Parameters:
        request - request object detailing the type of resource to retrieve.
        Returns:
        CompletableFuture that upon completion will contain the connection details for all resources matching a type

      • getResourcesBySerialisedFormat

        public CompletableFuture<Map<LeafResource,ConnectionDetail>> getResourcesBySerialisedFormat(GetResourcesBySerialisedFormatRequest request)
        Description copied from interface: ResourceService
        Find all resources that match a particular data format. Resources of a particular data format may not share a type, e.g. not all CSV format records will contain employee contact details. This method allows clients to retrieve all the resources Palisade knows about that conform to one particular format. Note that this method can potentially return large $Maps with many mappings.
        Specified by:
        getResourcesBySerialisedFormat in interface ResourceService
        Parameters:
        request - the request detailing the specific format for retrieval
        Returns:
        a CompletableFuture that upon completion will contain the details on how to retrieve the resources

      • addResource

        public CompletableFuture<Boolean> addResource(AddResourceRequest request)
        Description copied from interface: ResourceService
        Informs Palisade about a specific resource that it may return to users. This lets Palisade clients request access to that resource and allows Palisade to provide policy controlled access to it via the other methods in this interface.
        Specified by:
        addResource in interface ResourceService
        Parameters:
        request - details of the resource that Palisade can manage access to
        Returns:
